Nominated MP Sarah Lekorere has said threats being issued to aspirants are real and the government should take them seriously.She on Saturday said the killing of Tiaty MP hopeful Pepe Kitambaa and Loyamorok MCA Fredrick Kibet in Baringo, demonstrates the seriousness of the threats. The two were shot dead by masked gunmen in Marigat town and their vehicles torched on Saturday morning.Lekorere (seated), who is vying for Laikipia North MP and who has been involved in physical confrontation with MP Mathew Lempurkel, condemned the killings. &ldquo;The threats directed at me are real. It is high time the security and the Interior ministry considered acting on the information,&rdquo; she said.